# Multilingual Sentiment Analysis using Transformers

This project demonstrates a multilingual sentiment analysis pipeline using a pre-trained transformer model (`cardiffnlp/twitter-xlm-roberta-base-sentiment`) to classify user opinions into three categories: **Negative**, **Mixed**, and **Positive**.

## 🔍 Overview

- 💬 **Input**: Raw text data in multiple languages.
- 🧠 **Model**: `twitter-xlm-roberta-base-sentiment` (Roberta-based multilingual model)
- 🧪 **Task**: Sequence classification with 3 sentiment labels.
- ⚙️ **Framework**: TensorFlow & HuggingFace Transformers.

## 📊 Example Dataset

```csv
Text                                     | Label
----------------------------------------|--------
"I love the product!"                   | Positive
"Not good at all."                      | Negative
"Wow, great service... not!"           | Negative
"Food was great, service was awful"    | Mixed
"C'est fantastique!"                    | Positive
"Terrible, terrible, terrible."        | Negative